[1]
Date: Mon, 6 Dec 1999 09:10:36 GMT
From: "Benny P Cherian (MEDMIC) 15 7159" <B.P.Cherian@mds.qmw.ac.uk>

The Collector mentioned in the post is the District Collector in each
district of India. This is the topmost civil administrator in each
district. They
have a lot of administrative powers and this is a post we inherited from
the
British, from the Indian Civil Service (ICS) as it was called during
colonial
days. Now the new name is INDIAN ADMINISTRATIVE SERVICES (IAS). This
is a group of efficient officials in India and they are not political
appointees.
--
Dr.Benny P Cherian
Dept of Microbiology,
